File: C:/Users/ashay/Downloads/Test/QR-Code-Generator\style.css
Error:
1.  **User Requirement**: The user explicitly requested the background color of the page to be green. The current `body` style sets it to `#262a2f`.
2.  **Syntax Error**: The `#imgBox` style sets `width: 100`. In CSS, width values typically require a unit (e.g., `px`, `%`, `em`, `rem`). `100` without a unit is often interpreted as `100px` in some contexts or simply ignored, preventing it from taking up 100% of the parent's width as likely intended. It should be `width: 100%`.

Fixed code:
```css
*{
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    font-family :'Poppins';
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

body{
    background-color: green; /* Corrected to green as per user requirement */
}
.container{
    width : 400px;
    background-color: white;
    border-radius: 10px;  

    /* Centering the div */
    padding: 25px 35px;
    position:absolute;
    top : 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);  
}
.container p{
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.container input{
    width: 100%;
    height: 50px;
    border: 1px solid #494eea;
    outline: 0;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0 20px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}
.container button{
    width: 100%;
    height: 50px;
    border : 0;
    background-color: #494eea;
    color: white;
    outline: 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    margin:20px 0;
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
}
#imgBox{
    width: 100%; /* Corrected from width: 100 to width: 100% */
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
}

.invalid-input{
    border: 2px solid red;
    background-color: rgb(232, 132, 132);
    color: white;
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 5px;
}
```

